Enable realtime tracking information processing.Note that this may have performance impact.
When Piwik synchronization is enabled, the identifier is the same as the Piwik website id.
Determines how often log files are rotated.This option is required only for non-dynamic tracking.
Piwik analytics URL.When this option is set, all tracking information is passed to a Piwik instance.
Piwik API Token auth. It is used to make API calls and pass real client IP to Piwik.This token_auth must remain secure. Please do not share it!
Enable aggregation for visit statistics. This will improve statistics calculation time, but may have impact on save time.

Make sure this code is on every page of your website before the </body> tag.To track custom events, please uncomment the trackEvent string and replace
[name], [value], and [user_identifier] parameters with your values.
The script will log an event with the [name] name and optional [value].
To enable tracking on secure (HTTPS) websites HTTPS should also be enabledon the OroCRM web server.

Defines the actuality of the user's current password, whether the user can use it to log into the system, is in the process of the password change, or (for EE) their password needs to be reset because the user has too many failed login attempts.
The user's photo or other picture associated with the user.
The date of the user's birth.
The business units that the user has access to.
The one-time token generated for the password reset procedure.
An invitation email sending was failed
Defines whether the user is enabled to use the application.
People or third party systems with a specific set of credentials (login and password) that can be used to access the application.
How many times the user tried to log into the system using incorrect credentials.
The first name of the user.
The user's google ID used for the 'login using Google' functionality.
A set of users consolidated by one or more parameters. Instead of specifying each user one by one, you can specify a user group in filters and notification rules.
The unique identifier of a user group record
The name used to refer to a user group on the interface.
The roles assigned to the user group. Currently is not supported and will be removed.
The groups that the user belongs to.
The avatar must be in BMP, JPEG or PNG formats, and the file must be less than %file_size% in size
When this option is selected, an invitation email will be sent.
The date and time when the user last logged into the system.
The last name of the user.
The value of the Distinguished Name (DN) LDAP field. This field is not empty for the user only if their record has been imported from the LDAP server.
How many time the user logged into the system.
